signupForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {


event.preventDefault();

const fullName = document.getElementById("fullName").value;
const date = document.getElementById("date").value;
const address = document.getElementById("address").value;
const phone = document.getElementById("phone").value;
const email = document.getElementById("email").value;
const password = document.getElementById("password").value;

localStorage.setItem('FullName', fullName);
localStorage.setItem('Date', date);
localStorage.setItem('Address', address);
localStorage.setItem('Phone', phone);
localStorage.setItem('Email', email);
localStorage.setItem('Password', password);

alert('Sign up successful!');

});


You can book your place by visiting your nearest Catbook booking office. Find the office
closest to your using our <a href="Nearestoffice.html">
    Nearest Office </a> page. Remember to bring the tickets you are provided with by these
offices!


We want everyone to feel welcome and enjoy our cat-themed celebration! The venue has been
selected with accessibility in mind, offering step-free entrances and accessible restroom
facilities. If you have any specific accessibility needs or concerns, please reach out to us
in advance through our <a href="contact.html">Contact Us</a> page. We'll do our best to
accommodate your request so you can focus on the
festivities and feline fun!


ben:
Hello! I'm a Bengal cat, a striking breed known for my exotic appearance and playful nature.
My breed's origins can be traced back to the 1960s when a domestic cat was bred with a wild Asian Leopard Cat.
I have a muscular build and a sleek body, perfect for agile movements and impressive leaps.
My coat comes in various colors, including brown, silver, and snow, each with its unique allure.
Overall, I'm a captivating companion for those who appreciate a touch of the wild combined with the warmth of a
loving pet.

Greetings! I am a British Shorthair, a dignified and charming breed of cat.
My breed's roots trace back to ancient Rome when I was brought to Britain by the Romans.
My rounded face, sturdy build, and dense coat are some of my most recognizable features.
I come in a wide array of colors and patterns, including blue, silver, black, and tabby, among others.
Overall, I am a delightful addition to any home, bringing elegance, affection, and a touch of British charm
wherever I go.

Hello there, I'm a Munchkin cat, a unique and adorable breed known for my short legs.
The breed's origins can be traced back to Louisiana in the early 1990s, where a short-legged cat named Blackberry
was found.
My breed got its name from the Munchkin characters in 'The Wizard of Oz' due to our resemblance to them with our
short stature.
I come in a variety of colors and patterns, from solid colors to tabby and everything in between.
Overall, I may be short in stature, but I'm big on personality and love, bringing joy and laughter to any home
lucky enough to have me.

Hello there! I'm a Scottish Fold, a unique and charming breed of cat.
My distinctive feature is my folded ears, which give me an adorable and distinctive appearance.
I come in a variety of colors and patterns, including tabby, solid, bicolor, and more.
I owe my origins to a single barn cat named Susie, who lived on a farm in Scotland in the 1960s. She had the
natural genetic mutation that caused her ears to fold forward.
Overall, I'm a delightful addition to any home, bringing joy, companionship, and plenty of adorable antics to
brighten your day.